@endnode


@node "Ben—tigen" "What does the program need?"
@next "Introduction"
@prev "Install"



You need for the program:

 -AREXX

 -MCP + MCP-Guruhistory + MCP.gurudat

 -rexxtricks.library (V?)

 -an AMIGA (MC68xxx)

GC2EMail needs:

 -GuruStatistix-Script V1.48+

 -rexxreqtools.library

GuruStatistixPrefs and GStat(Gui)Prefs:

 -MPGui

Attention!  Attention!  Attention!  Attention!  Attention!  Attention!  Attention!

With Version V1.60+ I`ve splitted the versionnumber of GuruStatistix.lha-archiv
from GuruStatistix-program, because i`ve developed GC2EMail.
Now the version of the GuruStatistix.lha-archiv depends on changes of
GuruStatistix-programm, GC2EMail, GuruStatistix(GUI) and other changes.
@endnode


@node "Install" "How to Install"
@next "Introduction"
@prev "Main"


Installing is very easy:

only double click on Install Icon of your language

2 languages are avaible:

german

      and

english


There are some things to be observed that GuruStatistix can be run safely:

1: Choose mcp.gurudat-file with filename, because i have not written a routine
to control if a filename is given for mcp.gurudat

2: And choose a fileviewer with filename that GuruStatistix can display its
rendered datas after the work is done.
@endnode

@node "Introduction" "Introduction"
@prev "Install"
@next "Prefs"


GuruStatistix V1.82 is an AREXX-program and its freeware. It uses the
mcp-guruhistory-file.

For what is GuruStatistix? GuruStatistix analyse the Guruhistory for the
following things:

    -when was the first guru
    -how many gurus you have produced
    -what causes of guru and how often
    -the tasks that produces errors and how often
    -the days of registered gurus and how often at these days

@endnode


@node "Prefs" "Prefs"
@prev "Introduction"
@next "contact"

The preferences for this file can be found in ENV:gurustatistix.prefs
it can edit with all ASCII-Editors like GOLDED

The lines of the file have the following meaning:

1. line: path for the locale-file
2. line: path and filename of mcp.gurudat
3. line: path and filename of your favourite textfileviewer
4. line: path and filename of Guruhistory
5. line: path of GuruCharts-files
6. line: don`t change this line!!! Its data for internal calculations

@endnode

@node "Locales" "Locales"
@prev "prefs"
@next "Requirements"

The gurustatistix.catalog-file is an ASCII-File and can be edit with every
texteditor like GoldEd.

@endnode


